Crud Operations:

Create: This operation involves adding new entries to a database. For example, inserting a new row into a SQL table or a new document into a MongoDB collection.

Read: This operation is used to retrieve data from the database. It can involve querying the database for specific records or obtaining a set of records that match certain criteria.

Update: This operation involves modifying existing data in the database. This could be changing a single record, a group of records, or even all records that match a certain condition.

Delete: This operation removes data from the database. It could be a single record, multiple records, or all records that meet certain conditions.

MongoDB Commands: 

show dbs---- to show all dbs
use "database name" -- to switch into database
show collections --- to show all the collections into that database in which you have switched
db.collectionName..find()---- to find specific collection into database

1  -To Insert
db.collectionName.insertMany([
  { name: "Jane Smith", age: 25, position: "Data Analyst" },
  { name: "Alice Johnson", age: 28, position: "Product Manager" }
])

-----to insert many data into specific collection

db.collectionName.insertOne({ name: "John Doe", age: 30, position: "Software Engineer" })----- to insert one collection 

2 - To Read:
db.collectionName.find() ----to fetch all the documents
db.collectionName.find({age: 28}) --- to read specific one 

3 - To Update:
db.employees.updateOne(
  { _id: ObjectId("66026438302a620c28417a30") },
  { $set: { name: "Harsha" } }
)
----- to update just one

db.employees.updateMany(
  { age: 25 },
  { $set: { position: "AI Engineer" } }
);---- to update many

4 - To delete
 db.employees.deleteOne({ 
  _id: ObjectId("66026b1b59d33738551f8df3") 
});
 --- to delete one

db.employees.deleteMany({ 
  age: 28 
});


to delete many



to see the endpoint results: http://localhost:8000/